The latest MSTest is **4.2.2**. Here are the breaking changes that affect your project:

## 1. `[ExpectedException]` is removed (build error)

This is the biggest issue — your two test methods use `[ExpectedException]`, which no longer exists in v4. Replace with `Assert.ThrowsExactly<T>()`:

```csharp
// Before
[ExpectedException(typeof(ArgumentNullException))]
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_NullInput_ThrowsArgumentNull()
{
    Validate(null);
}

// After
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_NullInput_ThrowsArgumentNull()
{
    Assert.ThrowsExactly<ArgumentNullException>(() => Validate(null));
}
```

## 2. `Assert.IsTrue(true)` triggers warning MSTEST0032

In v4, this analyzer is promoted from Info → **Warning**. Your `Validate_ValidInput_Succeeds` test will produce a build warning. Replace with a meaningful assertion or remove it.

## 3. Other changes (likely not affecting you)

- `TestMethodAttribute.Execute` → `ExecuteAsync` (only if you subclass it)
- `ClassCleanupBehavior` enum removed
- `TestContext.Properties` is now `IDictionary<string, object>`
- `TestTimeout` enum removed
- `Assert.ThrowsException` removed (use `Assert.ThrowsExactly`)
- Dropped .NET < 8 support (you're already on net8.0 ✓)

## To upgrade

Update `TestProject.csproj`:
```xml
<PackageReference Include="MSTest" Version="4.2.2" />
```

Then refactor `[ExpectedException]` usages to `Assert.ThrowsExactly<T>()`. Want me to apply these changes?
